commit_list.message:
optimize traverse_shares a little

so it doesn't call p2pool twice for each share

Revert "bip0034 compatibility"

This reverts commit fa23ff200d41d4a025ed3394511a7c78e9068c56.

As the merged mining coinbase can now be anywhere

Merge remote-tracking branch 'forrestv/mm_anywhere'

better solution by ForrestV

updated midvalues in the proof test

all pass now

extra trace

to aid me with writing tests

re-created the share data in proof.t

How did I do it?

first, increased verbosity on trace to let me know what the getauxblock
response was (patch to follow).

Then I cut that line off from a logfile and put it in as the first line of
__DATA__.

Then the second line of data was effectively this:

curl http://127.0.0.1:9332/web/share_data/000000000045ee37d908e594e11f2d8d7c026280c33e969cfa12d00ea01af20c | xxd -ps -c100000

Now I'll have to update all the tests manually :-S

bip0034 compatibility

This follows p2pool's change which now adds block height in the merged mining
coinbase. Only use with v2 blocks and with p2pool that supports them.
